{
  "stem": "25773.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We never knew who had survived, who has not survived, whether which house was hit.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Which-- that was very traumatic experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were, we were, we were in the shelters--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the shelter of your house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of our own house, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Afterwards, we were very lucky, because with minor damages, the flat was in order.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we all were not wounded or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- there were very bad times, because, you know, the rubble on the street, and the smell of the burning houses, and wood, and whatever.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then the Germans came, of course, and immediately started with the pronouncements, what has to be done, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the first ones, the first order for the, for the, for the, for the public, and they formed straightaway some sort of, some sort of working forces-- not only Jewish, but everybody-- to, to, to clean the rubble and clean the, the, the streets.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then there were pronouncements of-- there were, there were, very quite short time afterwards that the Jews have to be prepared themselves.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, took now to 1940, till it was-- we still lived in our own flat and all that things.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in 1940 sometime, there were already pronouncements that to the Jewish people, who in majority occupied the north of Warsaw, which was [NON-ENGLISH] and all sorts of things--",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which were completely-- almost completely occupied.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But not all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were quite a lot of Christian people who lived there, Polish people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was organized in this way that the Polish people who lived there had to, had to abandon the flats or houses.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were allowed to take all the [INAUDIBLE] with them, whatever they had.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
